    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="487"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/481.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister to Haiti</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Russell has been informed by the Dominican Minister for Foreign Affairs that
                    Haitian authorities at Cape Haitien have sent Desiderio Arias by sea 200 rifles
                    and 10,000 rounds of ammunition, and that a Dominican revolutionist left Cape
                    Haitien with the arms and ammunition. If after investigation you find this to be
                    true you will state to the Haitian Government that the United States naturally
                    resents any attempt to give aid to any internal disturbances in the Dominican
                    Republic, in the peace of which the United States is vitally interested on
                    account of its treaty relations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
